@database print_guide
@node Main "Print Section"



		 @{ "Print While Searching " link sea }
		 @{ "Print Envelope        " link env }
		 @{ "Print All Records     " link all }
		 @{ "Print Current Record  " link curr }
		 @{ "Table View            " link table }
		 @{ "Record View           " link record }
		 @{ "Form View             " link form }
@endnode

@node sea "Print While Searching"

Searching

       Synopsis: Will send data to printer when you use the
       search function.

       ShortCut- p  (LowerCase)

   You have the option to Output To Printer or a File. If you elect to
   output to a file you can  select  the  Path	and  Filename  with  a
   requester.The data will Output to the screen and the file.

   Selecting this function any data output from the next  search  will
   be output to the screen and to the printer in the format  you  have
   selected, Table View or Record View.

@endnode
@node env "Print Envelope"

Envelope

       Synopsis:Will output the selected fields to a Label or
      Envelope.

       ShortCut-   e  (LowerCase)


   You will be asked for the tab position and then it will  print  the
   current record Selected Fields.

See Select Fields from Organise Section.

@endnode
@node all "Print All Records"

All Records

       Sysnopsis: Prints all the records.

       ShortCut-  a  (LowerCase)

   This function will print all the records in	the  format  that  you
   have selected.

@endnode
@node curr "Print Current Record"

Current Record

       Synopsis: Prints Current Record

       ShortCut-  c  (LowerCase)

   Prints Current Record in the format you have chosen
@endnode
@node table "Table View"

Table View

       Synopsis: Print Format

       ShortCut  t  (LowerCase)

   Prints  selected  fields  horizontally  accross  the  Paper.  After
   reaching 65 lines you will be asked to insert a new sheet of paper.
   If you use tractor feed then set your printer to  the  top  of  the
   next page.
@endnode

@node record "Record View" Record View

       Synopsis: Print Format

       ShortCut  r  (LowerCase)

   Prints Selected fields vertically down the paper.
@endnode
@node form "Form View"

       Synopsis: Print Format

       Shortcut f (LowerCase)

    Prints all fields as they appear on the  screen.  Saying  that  it
    will not display Bevel Boxes etc just the field Text and Data.

@endnode

